Ireland Homelessness Analytics
End-to-End Data Analytics Capstone Project

An end-to-end data analytics project exploring regional homelessness patterns across Ireland using official public datasets.

The project transforms fragmented government datasets into an integrated analytical model through data validation, standardisation, SQL modelling and interactive Power BI dashboards.

Project Objectives

The project was designed to answer the following business questions:

Which Irish regions experience the highest homelessness rates relative to population?
Which demographic groups are most affected?
Is there an observable association between homelessness, housing affordability and rent pressure?
How should unemployment and regional geography be interpreted alongside homelessness statistics?
